textRun.content: Community 43 allows me the opportunity to escape and be my own person. I have been able to build on my cooking skills with the head chef here at the community kitchen. It gives me freedom and gets me up every morning. Staff and peers are friendly, supportive and help me reach my goals. Everyone is genuinely kind. When I was away for some time, I was welcomed back with open arms. They all really missed me when I was gone. I feel cared for here at Community 43.

Coming to Community 43 has allowed me to have a life, a life that I am proud of. In the past, I’ve had a dark cloud over my head, and I could not connect with others, at all. I gave up on my hopes and dreams altogether. I’ve been to many similar programs in the past, but Community 43 is one of a kind. Joy, connection and love bring me to life and that’s what I get here. My hopes and dreams have come alive. Community 43 holds a freedom that no other programs have. This is a place of acceptance. The staff here really listen to us and respect us – they love us. Through this loving community, I have learned how to love myself. I really feel like when I come here, I try to be the best I can be! I continue to receive on-going guidance to keep getting better. If you come here, Community 43 will allow you to lead your life and help guide you to achieve your goals. For example, I used to sing. I haven’t sung in ages and no one in the world could get me to sing a single note. Yet, here at Community 43, I’m singing and performing again. People here back me up and shower me with support. For those that are thinking about joining: Come show us who you are, be who you are, get up, shine, rise, and be a series of miracles; here at Community 43.

My experience with Community 43 has been one of discovery and healing. As a member of the mental health community here in Phoenix for over 20 years, I have been exposed to many different programs. What I have accomplished in just a few months here has exceeded my growth in most programs I have attended.
Community 43 has treated me with no more than stellar respect as a member and are working with me in developing the skills I need to accomplish my daily and lifelong goals.

My confidence has grown tremendously and they have helped me regain what I thought I had lost….Hope. Hope in a bright future. Hope to return to steady employment. And hope to be the family member and friend that I have always wanted to be.
I look forward to growing with Community 43 and seeing what new learning opportunities come next!!!

My entire life shifted in immeasurable ways; my dreams I’ve often doubted I now see their possible potential. That's what keeps me coming back to Community 43. Through Community 43, I have been able to rebuild my foundation stronger and build my life again. I am part of this place. I have grown and changed in the most amazing ways and see that I am truly capable of great things.

Community 43 has changed my life. The people I have met here have changed my life for the better and I feel like we have all become a family here. The love and support I have received exceeded all expectations. People here believe in me; people here care for me; people here have watched me grow into the man I am and have become. Since coming here my mental health has improved significantly and I actually have the motivation to get up and show up as much as I can. I love coming to Community 43 and it will forever be a part of me.

Being a member of Community 43 is an ongoing great experience for me. There is a variety of activities, the Art Unit being my favorite; although the Horticulture, Culinary, Computer, and Music Units have been surprisingly fun and informational. Lunch is available daily and our chef (not fry cook) serves excellent healthy meals with a menu the members make up weekly.  But the very best thing that is offered is staff and peer availability, you don’t have to wait 2 weeks to see someone in the Mental Health Field. The benefit that helps me the most is being with my “true peers,” in a safe place where you can be open with other members who have walked in your shoes, relating, and interacting with you on a very deep personal level.

Coming to Community 43 gives me a sense of purpose every day. We as members have input on how the community grows and functions. I have a sense of control over my life which allows me to help influence the community here. Community 43 instills a sense of responsibility within me. I help with the horticulture center, and I have been able to co-facilitate classes. Community 43 is a place you come to learn about different fields of trade, as I have participated in creative employment opportunities to sell my artwork and jewelry. Yes, it’s a day program for mental health needs, but it helps train you to live in the real world independently (budget, healthy eating, computer skills, etc.). Community 43 treats the whole person here rather than just what they are diagnosed with. Members and staff are so intertwined, it is so cool how you can’t distinguish between the staff and members. The stigma is lessened. C43 is beneficial because they let you lead your own healing journey with support and care. You feel in control of your life.

To me, C43 is a place where people from all walks of life are brought together by a desire to rise above their limitations. When my personal struggle with mental and physical illness progressed to a debilitating level, I lost my sense of identity, purpose, and ultimately worth. C43 not only helps by providing the skills to better manage my symptoms but it’s their belief in me that’s made the biggest difference in my life. They’ve helped me realize my value regardless of any limitations. Feeling like a respected participant in a community gives me a sense of pride and responsibility to show up for C43 like they continuously show up for me. I haven’t felt hope in many years. Now I can see, and am working toward, an exciting future.
